Part Name: 24" x 36" x .177" Clear Acrylic Green Edge Sheet
Functional Description: I purchased this and cut to a window frame size piece that separates the external environment from my apartment interior.  I cut a hole in the acrylic to accept a hose that connects to a fan on the shelf extension of a rolling cabinet. The hose interfaces with fan on one size that draws out  the  smoke generated from laser engraving and the other end of the hose is connected to the hole cut into the acrylic sheet that acts as a barrier between the outside (for  venting) and the interior of my apartment.  The laser engraver enclosure contains the smoke particulates and the fan evacuates the smoke particulates.

I purchased this first set of PVC pipe to use as part of the shaker bar assembly I designed to vibrate shellac off of the walnet ornamental ribs during the drying process.
